WEBVTT

00:08.269 --> 00:09.661
- Previously on
"Dark Winds"...

00:09.792 --> 00:11.707
[dramatic music]

00:11.837 --> 00:15.711
- Out here, sometimes the best
protection isn't your .38.

00:15.841 --> 00:17.756
- Get down!
[gunshots]

00:17.887 --> 00:19.497
[whooshing]
[horse neighs]

00:19.628 --> 00:21.847
- She thinks she's encountered
a dark spirit.

00:21.978 --> 00:23.545
- Young, pregnant girl came.

00:23.675 --> 00:25.416
Just wanna make sure
she's not in any trouble.

00:25.547 --> 00:27.288
- Why is it every time
that you get a feeling,

00:27.418 --> 00:29.116
it always ends up
being more work for me?

00:29.246 --> 00:30.943
- Would you wanna stay
with Joe and I?

00:31.074 --> 00:32.206
- This was your son's room?

00:32.336 --> 00:35.513
- The oil field.
This is where I lost my boy.

00:35.644 --> 00:37.211
- I'm sorry about your son.

00:37.341 --> 00:38.560
- You can cut the act.
I know you're FBI.

00:38.690 --> 00:40.301
- You're FBI?

00:40.431 --> 00:41.563
- Left the bureau.

00:41.693 --> 00:42.520
- Thinkin' about
stayin' a while?

00:42.651 --> 00:44.740
- Keepin' my options open.

00:44.870 --> 00:46.481
- Well, we could always use
your help around here.

00:46.611 --> 00:50.485
♪

00:54.184 --> 00:57.100
[mysterious music]

00:57.231 --> 01:04.150
♪

01:32.179 --> 01:35.312
- Natalie, it's Leaphorn,
do you copy?

01:35.443 --> 01:38.446
- Go ahead, Lieutenant.

01:38.576 --> 01:40.317
- Call Sheriff Sena,
tell him we tracked

01:40.448 --> 01:43.407
the suspect to a trailer
about an hour south

01:43.538 --> 01:46.758
of Rough Rock
between Pinon and Chinle.

01:51.154 --> 01:52.590
Natalie, do you copy, over?

01:52.721 --> 01:54.636
- Copy.

01:54.765 --> 01:57.073
[garbled] Sheriff Sena--
find him, wait for backup.

01:57.204 --> 02:00.642
Do not approach the suspect.

02:00.772 --> 02:04.036
- They're about
2 to 3 hours away, best case.

02:06.691 --> 02:09.824
- I am tired of
chasin' this guy.

02:13.959 --> 02:16.527
[dramatic music]

02:16.658 --> 02:23.578
♪

03:15.804 --> 03:17.066
[banging]

03:17.197 --> 03:19.286
Navajo Tribal Police!
Come out!

03:19.416 --> 03:22.071
Keep your hands
where we can see 'em!

04:02.242 --> 04:04.940
[metronome ticking]

04:15.690 --> 04:17.082
Down, now!

04:31.227 --> 04:38.147
♪

04:52.640 --> 04:55.556
[dramatic guitar music]

04:55.686 --> 05:02.302
♪

05:43.604 --> 05:46.824
[The Allman Brothers Band's
"Midnight Rider"]

05:46.955 --> 05:53.570
♪

05:55.224 --> 05:57.835
- ♪ Well, I've got to run

05:57.966 --> 06:00.795
♪ To keep from hiding

06:00.925 --> 06:06.453
♪ And I'm bound
to keep on riding ♪

06:06.583 --> 06:11.762
♪ I've got one more
silver dollar ♪

06:11.893 --> 06:15.287
♪ But I'm not gonna
let 'em touch me, no ♪

06:15.418 --> 06:20.554
♪ Not gonna let 'em touch
the Midnight Rider ♪

06:20.684 --> 06:22.077
♪ Mm

06:24.514 --> 06:26.429
[horse grunting]

06:28.997 --> 06:32.566
♪ And I don't own
the clothes I'm wearing ♪

06:32.696 --> 06:34.132
- [shouts]

06:34.263 --> 06:39.573
- ♪ And the road
goes on forever ♪

06:39.703 --> 06:45.274
♪ And I got one more
silver dollar ♪

06:45.405 --> 06:48.756
♪ But I'm not gonna
let 'em catch me, no ♪

06:48.886 --> 06:54.109
♪ Not gonna let 'em catch
the Midnight Rider ♪

06:56.154 --> 06:58.026
♪ Mm

06:58.156 --> 07:05.120
♪

07:15.217 --> 07:17.132
- What happened?

07:17.262 --> 07:20.048
- I was attacked.

07:20.178 --> 07:22.311
- By what?

07:22.442 --> 07:24.879
- [whispering] Aliens.

07:28.448 --> 07:32.321
It might've been a sheep.

07:32.452 --> 07:33.844
- I'm taking you
to the hospital.

07:33.975 --> 07:35.455
What's this?

07:35.585 --> 07:38.066
- The rest of me.

07:38.196 --> 07:40.068
- Oh.

07:40.198 --> 07:41.808
- Yeah.

07:46.640 --> 07:49.120
[tires screeching]

07:49.251 --> 07:50.513
- [screams]

07:50.644 --> 07:52.515
I'm sorry!

07:59.783 --> 08:02.482
- [on TV] April 15.

08:04.788 --> 08:06.964
April 15.

08:07.095 --> 08:10.707
[TV chatter continues]

08:23.894 --> 08:25.200
- Emma Leaphorn?

08:28.725 --> 08:30.161
He's out of surgery.

08:30.292 --> 08:31.380
I'll let you know
when you can see him.

08:31.511 --> 08:33.294
- Thank you.

08:36.864 --> 08:38.342
- [on TV]
You are watching coverage

08:38.474 --> 08:41.869
of the '71
draft lottery drawing

08:41.999 --> 08:44.480
from the Selective Service
headquarters.

08:44.611 --> 08:46.526
The first birthdate
selected...

08:46.656 --> 08:48.571
[vending machine whirring]

08:50.921 --> 08:54.534
[foreboding music]

08:54.664 --> 08:55.709
- [speaking Diné]

08:58.102 --> 08:59.234
[grunts]

09:20.298 --> 09:23.258
[tool clicking]

09:24.520 --> 09:26.609
- Joe!

09:26.740 --> 09:28.655
Joe!
- Yeah?

09:28.785 --> 09:30.613
- It's Emma.
Something happened.

09:30.744 --> 09:33.398
[tense music]

09:33.529 --> 09:36.967
♪

09:37.098 --> 09:38.708
- Emma.

09:46.368 --> 09:49.023
- [speaking Diné]

09:52.243 --> 09:54.289
- [speaking Diné]
- [chuckles]

09:57.161 --> 10:01.688
- I'm OK,
just a bump on the head.

10:01.818 --> 10:03.994
I'm ready to go home,

10:04.125 --> 10:06.431
but the doctor wants
to go over X-rays with me.

10:06.562 --> 10:08.042
- OK.

10:08.172 --> 10:10.131
- He's treating me like
one of his regular patients

10:10.261 --> 10:11.480
and not like an Ind--

10:11.611 --> 10:14.657
- Hey. Hey.

10:14.788 --> 10:16.833
[whispering] I got you.

10:22.230 --> 10:23.623
[knock on door]

10:25.494 --> 10:27.322
- Excuse me, Lieutenant.
- Yeah.

10:30.151 --> 10:32.240
- Mrs. Leaphorn.

10:32.370 --> 10:33.763
- [speaking Diné]

10:40.770 --> 10:42.467
[police radio chatter]

10:42.598 --> 10:44.687
- The victim was Navajo,

10:44.818 --> 10:47.734
came in for
his cancer treatments.

10:52.434 --> 10:55.176
That stuff really work?

10:55.306 --> 10:58.658
- Yeah, well enough.

10:58.788 --> 11:01.878
- His name was Emerson Charley.

11:02.009 --> 11:04.011
You knew him?

11:04.141 --> 11:08.580
- Recognize the name.
Brother was Dillon Charley.

11:08.711 --> 11:13.150
Ran a church on the rez, called
themselves People of Darkness.

11:13.281 --> 11:17.589
Killed a couple of years ago
in a car accident.

11:17.720 --> 11:19.417
Year before he died,
he predicted

11:19.548 --> 11:23.770
something bad was gonna happen
out of the Drumco oil well.

11:23.900 --> 11:26.381
- You talking about
that explosion,

11:26.511 --> 11:29.993
killed those six men,

11:30.124 --> 11:31.952
your boy?

11:32.082 --> 11:33.388
- Yeah.

11:33.518 --> 11:35.216
- Yeah, well,

11:35.346 --> 11:37.871
I figure this thing
had a leak in the gas line.

11:38.001 --> 11:39.568
You knick the line,

11:39.699 --> 11:41.875
and then the engine heats up
and ignites the gas.

11:42.005 --> 11:45.705
And the next thing you know,
you know.

11:53.147 --> 11:54.975
- You said this went up
about 10:00?

11:55.105 --> 11:58.413
- About.

11:58.543 --> 12:00.720
- What time was
his appointment?

12:03.331 --> 12:04.811
- 7:00.

12:04.941 --> 12:07.944
- So the truck had been here
nearly three hours,

12:08.075 --> 12:09.641
sitting here.

12:09.772 --> 12:11.382
- Assuming he wasn't
on Indian time.

12:11.513 --> 12:14.124
- Engine would have
been cold by then.

12:14.255 --> 12:16.344
The engine was cold.

12:16.474 --> 12:18.520
What was the accelerant?

12:24.613 --> 12:26.441
Let me borrow your flashlight.

12:28.399 --> 12:31.272
[soft dramatic music]

12:31.402 --> 12:38.105
♪

12:49.420 --> 12:53.250
- You think he mighta lost an
earring when he got blowed up?

13:09.789 --> 13:11.399
What's that?

13:11.529 --> 13:12.922
- Timer spring.

13:17.971 --> 13:19.668
Won't be the only piece
of bomb you find

13:19.799 --> 13:22.845
if you look close enough.

13:22.976 --> 13:25.500
- Oh, now--now--
now wait a quick minute.

13:25.630 --> 13:28.938
That--that man was dying
of cancer, Lieutenant,

13:29.069 --> 13:31.723
had less than two months,
according to his doctor.

13:31.854 --> 13:33.073
Who'd want to blow him up?

13:33.203 --> 13:34.639
- Who and why?

13:34.770 --> 13:36.816
- Oh, God damn it.

13:39.470 --> 13:41.429
This is not how I wanted
to start my day.

13:41.559 --> 13:43.561
- Man has a son.

13:43.692 --> 13:46.738
Name is Tomas.
Lives out by Red Mesa.

13:46.869 --> 13:50.481
Start there,
tell him what happened.

13:50.612 --> 13:53.267
See if I can figure out
the why of it.

13:53.397 --> 13:55.312
You might want to take
a closer look at that truck,

13:55.443 --> 13:57.749
see if you can get
a line on who.

14:04.408 --> 14:06.193
[police radio chatter]

14:12.025 --> 14:14.114
[engine shuts off]

14:14.244 --> 14:16.507
[chicken clucking]
[Joe sighs]

14:19.815 --> 14:23.601
- You OK?

14:23.732 --> 14:26.082
- This whole family
needs to have a ceremony.

14:26.213 --> 14:27.997
- Again?

14:28.128 --> 14:32.175
You had it your way,
I'd never leave ceremony.

14:32.306 --> 14:35.570
- It's not normal
for us to be around

14:35.700 --> 14:37.920
so much death and violence.

14:38.051 --> 14:40.357
We have to stay in Hózhó.

14:55.764 --> 14:58.506
And what you went through
this morning scared you.

14:58.636 --> 15:01.030
It scared me too.

15:04.294 --> 15:07.210
- This family needs to
be put back in balance.

15:07.341 --> 15:09.343
We're having a ceremony.

15:09.473 --> 15:12.389
[soft music]

15:12.520 --> 15:13.651
♪

15:13.782 --> 15:15.827
[door slams]

15:23.183 --> 15:25.968
[dramatic music]

15:26.099 --> 15:32.583
♪

15:33.628 --> 15:35.543
[tires screeching]

15:35.673 --> 15:37.719
[engine accelerating]

15:39.547 --> 15:41.636
[tires screeching]

15:45.248 --> 15:46.858
- Go ahead, Bernie.
Whatcha got?

15:46.989 --> 15:49.078
- I'm in pursuit of
a male Navajo, 20s,

15:49.209 --> 15:52.647
headed North of the Old Road,
a couple miles east of Kayenta.

15:52.777 --> 15:53.996
I think it's Dean Bitsuie.

15:54.127 --> 15:55.563
- 10-4.

15:55.693 --> 15:57.347
What'd he do now?
Steal another car?

15:57.478 --> 15:59.088
- Worse.

15:59.219 --> 16:01.090
Tell Leaphorn
I'm gonna be late.

16:12.667 --> 16:15.670
[dog barking]

16:18.890 --> 16:21.893
[fly buzzing]

16:24.374 --> 16:28.117
- [speaking Diné]

16:33.775 --> 16:36.038
- [giggling]

16:39.955 --> 16:42.653
- Lieutenant, Bernie called in.

16:42.784 --> 16:44.742
She's gonna be late.

16:44.873 --> 16:46.092
Take it easy on her.

16:46.222 --> 16:48.007
- Guess I'll handle roll call.

16:58.408 --> 17:00.236
All right, everyone,
listen up.

17:00.367 --> 17:03.500
Felix, got another complaint
from Gerald Nez.

17:03.631 --> 17:05.241
Says somebody's
illegally dumping

17:05.372 --> 17:07.113
RV waste on his property.

17:07.242 --> 17:09.419
Let's see what's going on, OK?

17:09.550 --> 17:10.768
- Yes, sir.

17:10.898 --> 17:13.075
- Greetings, Earthlings.

17:13.205 --> 17:14.076
- Sit.

17:17.819 --> 17:19.080
In a chair, Begaye.

17:23.477 --> 17:25.305
- [chuckles]

17:29.570 --> 17:31.659
- You heard about the truck bomb
in Skunkborough yesterday?

17:31.789 --> 17:32.660
- Who?

17:32.790 --> 17:35.097
- Victim's Navajo.

17:35.228 --> 17:37.578
Elder named Emerson Charley.

17:37.708 --> 17:39.754
- [speaking Diné]
Thought those kinds of things

17:39.884 --> 17:41.538
only happened in big cities.

17:41.669 --> 17:43.323
- Yeah, well,
there's monsters everywhere.

17:43.453 --> 17:44.889
- My uncle knew Emerson.

17:45.020 --> 17:47.240
Said he only had
a few months to live.

17:47.370 --> 17:49.329
- I'm gonna go talk to his son,
Tomas...

17:49.459 --> 17:52.723
[horse neighs]
And find out...

17:52.854 --> 17:55.204
What the?

18:12.134 --> 18:14.267
- Oh come, Bernadette,
why you gotta lock me up, man?

18:14.397 --> 18:16.225
- What'd I tell you last time,
Dean?

18:16.356 --> 18:19.010
Right, that next time,
I was gonna lock you up.

18:19.141 --> 18:23.014
Well, guess what?
It's next time.

18:23.145 --> 18:24.799
- Come on, [speaking Diné].
Have a heart.

18:24.929 --> 18:26.235
- Grow a brain.

18:26.366 --> 18:28.585
- [speaking Diné], Dean.
What'd he do this time?

18:28.716 --> 18:31.066
- Before or after he got
my car stuck in the sand?

18:31.197 --> 18:33.373
- All right, we're done here.
Let's get to it.

18:40.249 --> 18:43.078
That an Appaloosa?

18:43.209 --> 18:45.820
- How about
"Good job, Sergeant"?

18:45.950 --> 18:47.387
- Well, how 'bout you ask
for help next time

18:47.517 --> 18:50.172
you have to ride a suspect in
on a horse.

18:50.303 --> 18:52.783
Hmm?

18:52.914 --> 18:55.134
When you're done here,
see what Steve has to say.

18:55.264 --> 18:58.615
[soft guitar music]

18:58.746 --> 19:00.574
- Well, sail on,
on Silver Girl.

19:00.704 --> 19:02.358
'Member me?

19:02.489 --> 19:04.012
- No.

19:04.143 --> 19:05.405
- You bought a horse
off my brother, Danny,

19:05.535 --> 19:07.842
like, three, four years ago.

19:07.972 --> 19:09.713
We met when you came
to pick him up.

19:09.844 --> 19:12.455
- Good luck.

19:12.586 --> 19:14.979
- Let me ask you something,
Sergeant Manuelito.

19:15.110 --> 19:16.590
Do you believe?

19:19.941 --> 19:22.639
[birds chirping]

19:32.040 --> 19:34.651
[door clicks, squeaks]

19:37.698 --> 19:40.570
[door squeaks, clicks]

19:40.701 --> 19:44.444
- [groans]

19:44.574 --> 19:47.186
[sighs]

19:52.756 --> 19:54.018
[neck cracks]

19:54.149 --> 19:56.238
[grunts]

20:08.990 --> 20:11.210
No last digit.

20:16.171 --> 20:18.434
- Have you found her?

20:21.611 --> 20:23.309
- Take a look.

20:24.875 --> 20:26.877
See that?

20:27.008 --> 20:29.010
Linda Maddox.

20:29.140 --> 20:31.273
Ring a bell?

20:31.404 --> 20:34.363
You think that could be her?

20:37.366 --> 20:38.454
[tense musical sting]

20:38.585 --> 20:40.369
- Is it?

20:40.500 --> 20:43.764
[chair squeaks]
- [chuckling]

20:43.894 --> 20:45.896
- Huevos rancheros
and your breakfast burrito.

20:46.027 --> 20:46.854
- Gracias.

20:46.984 --> 20:49.857
[soft tense music]

20:49.987 --> 20:53.513
♪

20:53.643 --> 20:55.166
[tense musical sting]

20:55.297 --> 20:56.733
- There's something else.

20:56.864 --> 20:59.475
The needle in the haystack...
[taps table]

20:59.606 --> 21:01.738
Just got a little shinier.

21:01.869 --> 21:04.480
Hey, trust me.

21:06.395 --> 21:08.528
So...

21:08.658 --> 21:11.270
what're you doing out here
in Indian country anyway?

21:11.400 --> 21:13.489
Vacation?

21:19.843 --> 21:22.672
- I need her to be found.

21:22.803 --> 21:29.766
♪

21:33.466 --> 21:37.165
- This is--this is--
[sighs]

21:37.296 --> 21:39.907
Relax, man.
[chuckles]

21:40.037 --> 21:41.996
We're close.

21:42.126 --> 21:44.433
We are close.

21:46.000 --> 21:48.742
I can feel it.

21:48.872 --> 21:52.963
I'm just gonna...wash my hands.

22:11.895 --> 22:13.549
[lock clicks]

22:15.725 --> 22:18.206
- It's, uh, occupied, pal.

22:18.337 --> 22:21.035
[hand dryer whirring]

22:30.740 --> 22:33.961
♪

22:34.091 --> 22:36.877
- Damn it, man.

22:37.007 --> 22:39.314
- Don't be scared.
- I'm scared for you, asshole.

22:39.445 --> 22:41.969
'Cause when I--I'm gonna--
[stammers]

22:42.099 --> 22:43.623
[gunshot]

23:21.661 --> 23:24.446
[Navajo song
playing over radio]

23:24.577 --> 23:31.540
♪

23:49.210 --> 23:50.559
[engine and music stop]

23:52.779 --> 23:55.042
- [speaking Diné]

23:55.172 --> 23:57.436
Nice bike.
- [speaking Diné]

24:00.439 --> 24:03.311
- Is your dad home? No?

24:03.442 --> 24:07.968
OK, well, if you see your dad,
you tell him I stopped by, OK?

24:08.098 --> 24:11.450
All right.
Be careful on that thing.

24:22.635 --> 24:24.114
[engine turns over]

24:24.245 --> 24:25.551
[Ray Price's "Invitation
to the Blues" on radio]

24:25.681 --> 24:27.770
- ♪ Received your invitation

24:27.901 --> 24:29.729
♪ To the blues

24:29.859 --> 24:32.122
♪

24:32.253 --> 24:35.082
- Your nephew's the one who's
been stealing your piñon nuts.

24:35.212 --> 24:38.389
- [speaking Diné]

24:40.783 --> 24:42.872
- I'm sorry, Másání.

24:43.003 --> 24:44.700
He didn't think you'd notice.

24:48.225 --> 24:53.622
- ♪ You took the laughter
from this world of mine ♪

24:56.233 --> 25:00.194
♪ Thanks to you,
the sun will never shine ♪

25:04.111 --> 25:09.203
- ♪ Walk the floor so much,
wore out my shoes ♪

25:11.379 --> 25:14.991
♪ Received your invitation

25:15.122 --> 25:17.428
♪ To the blues

25:19.343 --> 25:21.563
- You call me
if you need anything.

25:21.694 --> 25:23.522
- Yeah, I will.

25:25.480 --> 25:28.483
- Hey, a biligáanalady
wants to talk to you.

25:28.614 --> 25:30.398
- ♪ I just hope I'll never

25:30.529 --> 25:33.401
♪ Go through this much again

25:35.142 --> 25:39.755
♪ Lonely me,
I don't know what to do ♪

25:39.886 --> 25:41.278
- Jim Chee.

25:41.409 --> 25:43.585
[knocking on door]

25:43.716 --> 25:46.588
[pensive music]

25:46.719 --> 25:49.373
♪

25:49.504 --> 25:52.638
[door creaks open]

25:52.768 --> 25:54.553
Jim Chee,
here to see Mrs. Vines.

25:54.683 --> 25:56.206
- This way.

25:56.337 --> 26:03.344
♪

26:16.357 --> 26:18.141
Wait here.

26:32.329 --> 26:34.984
[birds chirping]

26:35.115 --> 26:37.639
[canister clanking]

26:45.778 --> 26:48.519
- You're younger
than I expected.

27:02.533 --> 27:04.797
- Should you be doing that?

27:04.927 --> 27:08.104
- Don't scold me, Mr. Chee.
We've only just met.

27:08.235 --> 27:09.758
Drink?

27:09.889 --> 27:12.500
- Coffee, if it's no problem.
[bell rings]

27:15.459 --> 27:18.506
- Gabriela, bring us
scotch and some coffee.

27:24.991 --> 27:27.297
- How can I help you,
Mrs. Vines?

27:27.428 --> 27:29.560
- Been a burglary here
a few days ago.

27:29.691 --> 27:32.346
Someone broke in, stole a box
from my husband's safe.

27:32.476 --> 27:35.566
I want you to get it and bring
it back before he comes home.

27:35.697 --> 27:38.134
He's on a hunting trip.
He'll be home in two days.

27:41.964 --> 27:43.139
- Thank you.

27:43.270 --> 27:45.707
- I'll pay you $500 now
and another $2,500

27:45.838 --> 27:47.753
when you bring me the box.

27:47.883 --> 27:49.189
- You report this
to the police?

27:49.319 --> 27:50.843
- My husband supported
the sheriff's opponent

27:50.973 --> 27:52.279
in the last election.

27:52.409 --> 27:54.063
He's not gonna lift
a finger to help us.

27:54.194 --> 27:55.891
And besides,
it's an Indian problem.

27:56.022 --> 27:58.111
That's why I called you.

28:00.679 --> 28:03.072
You ever heard of
the People of Darkness?

28:03.203 --> 28:05.205
- Should I have?

28:05.335 --> 28:08.774
- They're a mystical sect
out here in the desert,

28:08.904 --> 28:11.864
healers who have peyote
ceremonies and visions,

28:11.994 --> 28:13.822
all that Navajo type of thing.

28:13.953 --> 28:16.520
I believe they're responsible
for the burglary.

28:16.651 --> 28:18.653
- OK.

28:18.784 --> 28:19.959
What was in the box?

28:20.089 --> 28:21.221
- I don't know.

28:21.351 --> 28:22.962
And that makes
no difference to you.

28:23.092 --> 28:25.225
All you need to do is find it
and bring it back.

28:25.355 --> 28:27.096
- Sounds simple.

28:27.227 --> 28:28.445
- Couldn't be simpler.

28:28.576 --> 28:31.057
- Except nothing is.

28:31.187 --> 28:34.408
You're not telling me something,
Mrs. Vines.

28:34.538 --> 28:37.890
And I've found that when people
aren't telling me something,

28:38.020 --> 28:39.761
that's a good way to get hurt.

28:39.892 --> 28:43.417
- [soft, labored breathing]

28:43.547 --> 28:45.549
Don't agitate me, Mr. Chee.

28:45.680 --> 28:48.161
It affects my breathing.

28:48.291 --> 28:51.120
[hose hissing]

28:51.251 --> 28:53.949
[labored breathing]

28:55.429 --> 28:57.648
Come with me.

28:57.779 --> 29:00.347
[soft dramatic music]

29:00.477 --> 29:05.091
♪

29:05.221 --> 29:06.657
Last Wednesday,
in the middle of the night,

29:06.788 --> 29:09.008
Gabriela heard a noise,
came down here,

29:09.138 --> 29:13.055
saw the safe open
and Tomas Charley outside,

29:13.186 --> 29:15.362
sneaking away with
the box under his arm.

29:15.492 --> 29:17.233
Tomas' father, Emerson,
introduced my husband

29:17.364 --> 29:19.279
to the People of Darkness,

29:19.409 --> 29:22.935
then gave them money for a while
and then grew disenchanted.

29:23.065 --> 29:26.286
I think...

29:26.416 --> 29:28.984
I think this is their way
of getting back at him.

29:35.382 --> 29:39.125
- You sure these people
are Navajo?

29:39.255 --> 29:42.041
- Mr. Chee,
I don't want to punish anyone.

29:42.171 --> 29:44.347
I just want the box back.

29:44.478 --> 29:47.568
All you have to do is find
Tomas Charley and get it.

29:47.698 --> 29:50.614
Can you do that for me?

29:50.745 --> 29:53.661
- [sighs]

29:53.792 --> 29:55.794
- Please.

30:03.149 --> 30:04.628
- What if I can't find him?

30:04.759 --> 30:08.197
- Then you are $500 richer

30:08.328 --> 30:11.505
and not the man
I thought you were.

30:22.995 --> 30:24.518
Good.

30:27.390 --> 30:30.306
[upbeat guitar music]

30:30.437 --> 30:37.052
♪

30:45.887 --> 30:48.629
[birds chirping]
- [sighs]

31:02.469 --> 31:06.560
Told ya, the sheep that bit
my fingers off was an alien.

31:06.690 --> 31:08.562
That's how it got here.

31:26.667 --> 31:29.888
- Property of
the U.S. Air Force, hemp-head.

31:32.629 --> 31:34.588
- Wait.

31:40.594 --> 31:42.944
No way.

31:45.555 --> 31:47.340
Of course.

31:47.470 --> 31:49.168
That's what they
want us to think.

31:49.298 --> 31:50.821
I'm telling you.

31:50.952 --> 31:52.823
I saw a sheep come out
of here last night,

31:52.954 --> 31:57.480
a freaky sheep,
with horns, twisted and weird,

31:57.611 --> 31:59.830
probably trying to communicate
with the mother sheep.

32:02.268 --> 32:04.313
- You need to get yourself
straight, Steve.

32:04.444 --> 32:06.315
Get off all these substances.

32:06.446 --> 32:08.448
There's a Navajo man in there,

32:08.578 --> 32:10.406
and if you're not careful,
you're gonna kill him.

32:10.537 --> 32:12.147
Geez.

32:14.323 --> 32:15.585
For my trouble.

32:15.716 --> 32:17.065
- Wait.
- No.

32:19.372 --> 32:22.723
- What man?

32:22.853 --> 32:25.682
[Charley Pride's "Kiss an
Angel Good Mornin'" on radio]

32:25.813 --> 32:30.774
- ♪ They wonder how does a man
get to be this way? ♪

32:30.905 --> 32:33.473
♪

32:33.603 --> 32:37.129
♪ I've always got
a smilin' face ♪

32:37.259 --> 32:40.784
♪ Any time and any place

32:40.915 --> 32:42.786
♪ And every time
they ask me why ♪

32:42.917 --> 32:47.008
♪ I just smile and say

32:47.139 --> 32:51.795
♪ You've got to kiss an angel
good mornin' ♪

32:51.926 --> 32:56.887
♪ And let her know you think
about her when you're gone ♪

32:57.018 --> 32:59.716
♪ Kiss an angel good mornin'

32:59.847 --> 33:01.240
♪ And love her
like the devil ♪

33:01.370 --> 33:05.461
[sheep bleats]
♪ When you get back home

33:05.592 --> 33:08.334
[soft indistinct chatter]

33:18.561 --> 33:20.433
- Tomas Charley?

33:24.654 --> 33:26.091
- You police?
- No.

33:26.221 --> 33:27.831
I work for Mrs. Vines.

33:27.962 --> 33:29.268
- OK.

33:29.398 --> 33:31.313
Does she need a rug or what?

33:31.444 --> 33:33.272
- She needs the box
you stole from her husband.

33:33.402 --> 33:35.274
- I don't know what
you're talking about.

33:35.404 --> 33:37.711
- Listen, I don't give a damn
if you broke in there,

33:37.841 --> 33:39.321
stole that box.

33:39.452 --> 33:41.149
I'm just getting paid
to bring it back.

33:43.804 --> 33:45.588
Or you can come with me
to the sheriff.

33:49.940 --> 33:52.291
- That white man's a witch.

33:52.421 --> 33:54.075
He's killing my father.

33:54.206 --> 33:55.294
- How?

33:55.424 --> 33:57.296
- Cancer.

33:57.426 --> 33:59.472
- Witchcraft doesn't
cause cancer, Tomas.

33:59.602 --> 34:03.302
- My father told me
B.J. Vines cursed him.

34:03.432 --> 34:05.695
He told me to get that box,

34:05.826 --> 34:07.741
take it to the sacred place
we know.

34:07.871 --> 34:09.351
He said that there's
something in the box

34:09.482 --> 34:11.658
to reverse the spell.

34:11.788 --> 34:14.094
- This is, uh, People of
Darkness hocus pocus, isn't it?

34:14.226 --> 34:17.446
- Vines is People of Darkness,

34:17.577 --> 34:20.058
him and his
rich hippie friends.

34:20.188 --> 34:23.061
It's bad medicine now.

34:23.190 --> 34:25.018
White people medicine.

34:25.150 --> 34:27.891
- Where's the box?
- O-OK.

34:28.022 --> 34:31.112
OK.

34:31.243 --> 34:33.853
I left the box on the Malpaís.

34:33.984 --> 34:36.161
If my father hasn't gotten it
yet, it should still be there.

34:36.291 --> 34:37.553
- Bullshit.

34:37.684 --> 34:39.554
- I can draw you a map.

34:45.039 --> 34:47.085
- Make it a good one.

34:51.263 --> 34:54.135
[dramatic music]

34:54.266 --> 34:55.789
♪

35:02.361 --> 35:04.058
- Little out of
your jurisdiction,

35:04.189 --> 35:05.146
aren't you, Lieutenant?

35:05.277 --> 35:08.497
- [speaking Diné], Jim Chee.

35:08.628 --> 35:10.978
You buying rugs or looking
for a new old lady?

35:11.109 --> 35:14.547
- Hey, you borrowed a sense
of humor since I saw you last.

35:14.677 --> 35:16.592
Actually, I'm working.

35:16.723 --> 35:18.899
- Every hotel needs
a good manager, I guess.

35:19.029 --> 35:21.684
- For Mrs. Vines.

35:21.815 --> 35:23.382
- Wow.

35:23.512 --> 35:25.819
- She hired me to recover
some stolen property.

35:25.949 --> 35:27.647
What're you doing here?

35:27.777 --> 35:29.605
- Hear about the explosion
yesterday at the hospital?

35:29.736 --> 35:31.868
- Yeah, I heard there was
a gas leak in some rez wagon.

35:31.999 --> 35:33.305
- No, it was a car bomb.

35:33.435 --> 35:35.655
Killed an elder.
Emerson Charley.

35:35.785 --> 35:38.005
Looking for his son,
told he's here selling rugs.

35:38.136 --> 35:41.139
- Wait, not a Tomas Charley?

35:41.269 --> 35:42.836
- Yeah. Why?

35:42.966 --> 35:45.186
- He's the one that
broke into the Vines'.

35:45.317 --> 35:47.188
I was just talking to him.

35:47.319 --> 35:50.191
[soft dramatic music]

35:50.322 --> 35:57.285
♪

36:04.727 --> 36:08.557
Guess I scared him off.

36:08.688 --> 36:10.907
- What'd he take
from the Vines' house?

36:11.038 --> 36:13.867
- Box, uh, from the safe.
Don't know what's in it.

36:13.997 --> 36:15.651
- Tomas give you the box?

36:15.782 --> 36:18.654
- No, but he did tell me
where to find it, though.

36:18.785 --> 36:21.396
Drew me a--a map.

36:21.527 --> 36:22.658
Yeah.

36:30.100 --> 36:31.885
- I'll drive.

36:38.805 --> 36:41.503
- Better be careful that thing
don't melt in the sun.

36:41.634 --> 36:43.984
- It's a new synthetic polymer.

36:44.114 --> 36:45.246
Space Age, Joe.

36:45.377 --> 36:47.248
- So PI work pays enough
to stock up

36:47.379 --> 36:49.468
in space-age monkey suits?

36:49.598 --> 36:52.210
- Don't entice me with
your BIA police salary.

36:52.340 --> 36:56.301
- [chuckles]

36:56.431 --> 36:58.085
Given any more thought
to coming back?

36:58.216 --> 37:00.000
- To what?
Pound sand for a living?

37:00.130 --> 37:01.915
- You mean on the rez?

37:02.045 --> 37:04.483
- I mean, wherever sand grows.

37:04.613 --> 37:05.919
- Yeah.

37:06.049 --> 37:07.877
The rez is getting
more complicated.

37:08.008 --> 37:10.228
- When hasn't it?

37:18.105 --> 37:21.151
How's, uh, Bernadette?

37:21.282 --> 37:23.937
- Eh, got a new rookie
in the office.

37:24.067 --> 37:28.158
I think she might like
the roly-poly type.

37:28.289 --> 37:29.943
- Wait, you kidding?
- [laughs]

37:32.467 --> 37:34.643
She's still pissed off.

37:34.774 --> 37:36.689
- At who?

37:40.519 --> 37:43.739
Any advice on how to work
my way out of the doghouse?

37:43.870 --> 37:45.524
- I don't know,
maybe she'll snap out of it

37:45.654 --> 37:49.136
when she sees
that space-age fabric.

37:49.267 --> 37:52.531
- Couldn't hurt, though.

37:52.661 --> 37:53.662
Wait, could it?

37:53.793 --> 37:54.968
- Hurt?

37:55.098 --> 37:58.276
Shit, 'less you mean my eyes.

37:58.406 --> 38:01.191
'Ey?
[laughs]

38:03.324 --> 38:06.936
- You, you're something else,
Joe Leaphorn.

38:07.067 --> 38:08.982
[lock clicks]
[sheep bleats]

38:11.811 --> 38:13.073
[sheep bleating]

38:13.203 --> 38:15.293
- The hell's that, man?

38:15.423 --> 38:16.555
- [speaking Diné]

38:16.685 --> 38:19.645
- Relax, people,
it's just a sheep.

38:19.775 --> 38:22.256
- [speaking Diné],
who does it belong to?

38:22.387 --> 38:26.216
- I don't know,
but somebody will.

38:26.347 --> 38:28.349
I'll be at the trading post.

38:31.439 --> 38:34.355
[soft foreboding music]

38:34.486 --> 38:41.406
♪

38:50.110 --> 38:53.461
[sheep bleats]

38:53.592 --> 38:56.812
[upbeat Navajo music
playing over radio]

38:56.943 --> 39:03.602
♪

39:07.780 --> 39:09.912
[brakes screech]

39:11.740 --> 39:13.481
- You get it?
- Got it.

39:26.494 --> 39:27.843
[engine and music stop]

39:27.974 --> 39:30.846
[soft suspenseful music]

39:30.977 --> 39:37.418
♪

39:51.345 --> 39:52.607
There.

39:55.349 --> 40:02.400
♪

40:20.243 --> 40:21.549
- [sighs]

40:28.600 --> 40:31.559
[wind whooshes]

41:05.898 --> 41:08.944
[foreboding music]

41:09.075 --> 41:15.690
♪

41:47.896 --> 41:48.767
- What?

42:00.343 --> 42:02.998
- This belonged to my son.

42:05.914 --> 42:09.222
He wore it on the day he died.

42:10.832 --> 42:13.879
[wind whooshing]

42:17.491 --> 42:19.537
- That's some crazy
witchcraft shit right there.

42:22.322 --> 42:24.237
[gunshot]
Ah!

42:24.367 --> 42:27.196
[dramatic music]

42:27.327 --> 42:29.242
♪

42:29.372 --> 42:32.114
- Come on.
- [groaning]

42:33.986 --> 42:35.553
- Come on.

42:35.683 --> 42:38.425
- [groaning, whimpers]

42:41.341 --> 42:45.432
[groaning, panting]

42:45.563 --> 42:46.781
I'll be--I'll be okay.

42:46.912 --> 42:49.349
[gunshots]

42:49.479 --> 42:52.265
- OK, hold on.

42:57.966 --> 42:59.620
We got to get to the truck,
get the rifle.

43:02.144 --> 43:04.407
Hold this.

43:04.538 --> 43:06.061
[softly] Here.

43:06.192 --> 43:08.194
Here.

43:08.324 --> 43:09.717
All right.

43:09.848 --> 43:11.850
Try to get on top of him.
I'll come up from below.

43:14.983 --> 43:16.594
You ready?

43:18.813 --> 43:19.988
Go.

43:20.119 --> 43:24.297
♪

43:24.427 --> 43:27.256
[rapid gunshots]

43:34.437 --> 43:37.179
- [speaking Diné]

43:45.144 --> 43:46.232
- [grunts]

43:46.362 --> 43:52.891
♪

44:09.211 --> 44:10.996
- Shit.

44:11.126 --> 44:12.867
[grunts]

44:37.892 --> 44:38.937
- [grunts]

44:44.856 --> 44:46.335
[engine turns over]

44:49.469 --> 44:51.166
- You son of a bitch.

44:56.824 --> 44:58.347
[tires screeching]

44:58.478 --> 45:05.485
♪

45:14.363 --> 45:16.801
Chee. Chee.

45:16.931 --> 45:20.369
- [grunting, panting]

45:20.500 --> 45:23.111
- Come on, get up.

45:23.242 --> 45:26.158
Come on.
- [groans]

45:26.288 --> 45:27.681
- Sit, sit.

45:27.812 --> 45:29.596
Let me see.

45:29.727 --> 45:31.990
["Death Don't Have No Mercy"]

45:32.120 --> 45:34.601
Hold that tight.

45:34.732 --> 45:37.735
- [grunting]

45:40.128 --> 45:41.956
I get him?

45:42.087 --> 45:44.002
- No.

45:44.132 --> 45:46.744
- He get you?
- No.

45:46.874 --> 45:51.661
Can you walk?
Can you walk?

45:51.792 --> 45:53.489
- Can you give me a minute?

45:53.620 --> 45:59.191
- ♪ Well, death don't have
no mercy in this land ♪

45:59.321 --> 46:02.324
♪

46:02.455 --> 46:08.374
♪ I said death don't have
no mercy in this land ♪

46:08.504 --> 46:10.506
♪

46:10.637 --> 46:12.508
♪ Well, he'll come
to your house ♪

46:12.639 --> 46:15.337
♪ And he won't stay long

46:15.468 --> 46:19.733
♪ Look down the room, one of
your family will be gone ♪

46:19.864 --> 46:25.043
♪ Death don't have no mercy
in this land ♪

46:25.173 --> 46:27.654
♪

46:27.785 --> 46:31.527
♪ Well, he never take time
for vacation ♪

46:31.658 --> 46:33.703
♪ In this land

46:37.316 --> 46:40.188
Joe: I have to find out
who's behind this.

46:40.319 --> 46:41.973
I have to.

46:42.103 --> 46:45.541
♪

46:45.672 --> 46:47.108
Leaphorn sent me
to take your statement.

46:47.239 --> 46:50.198
No "How are you?
Good to see you."

46:50.329 --> 46:52.113
Joe: That boy said a blond man
blew up the well.

46:52.244 --> 46:55.508
Now suddenly we got a blond man
here killing people.

46:55.638 --> 46:57.553
Bern, he's here.

46:57.684 --> 47:00.643
[ Fire alarm ringing ]

47:00.774 --> 47:02.907
My son died
on what's now your property.

47:03.037 --> 47:04.212
That's got nothing
to do with me.

47:04.343 --> 47:06.736
The world needs to know
what is going on here.

47:06.867 --> 47:07.868
Emma:
So you can write something

47:07.999 --> 47:10.001
about "us poor Indians
on the rez."

47:10.131 --> 47:11.350
Bernadette:
What the hell's going on?

47:11.480 --> 47:15.006
It's the blond man.
I think he murdered my son.

47:15.136 --> 47:17.443
I am tired
of chasing this guy.

47:17.573 --> 47:18.792
Joe, Joe, Joe!

47:18.923 --> 47:20.359
This isn't about you.

47:20.489 --> 47:22.361
Bernadette: Joe Leaphorn
is like a father to me.

47:22.491 --> 47:25.538
The monsters ain't just
in the shadows.

47:25.668 --> 47:27.714
They're in broad
damn daylight.

47:27.845 --> 47:30.325
If we don't get him by sun-up,
he'll be gone forever.

47:30.456 --> 47:32.110
Joe:
I'm not going to lose him.

47:32.240 --> 47:34.982
♪
